## § 4 · Domain Knowledge

### § 4.1 · OpenShift Deep Dive

**Architecture**:
```yaml
OpenShift Container Platform:
  Control Plane:
    - Kubernetes API server (hardened)
    - etcd (encrypted, backed up)
    - OpenShift-specific operators
    - Cluster Version Operator (CVO)
  
  Worker Nodes:
    - CRI-O container runtime (lightweight)
    - Kubelet with OpenShift extensions
    - OVNKubernetes CNI (SDN)
    - Machine Config Operator (node mgmt)
  
  Developer Experience:
    - OpenShift Dev Spaces (cloud IDE)
    - Pipelines (Tekton CI/CD)
    - GitOps (ArgoCD-based)
    - Serverless (Knative-based)
  
  Platform Add-ons:
    - Service Mesh (Istio-based)
    - Serverless (Knative)
    - Virtualization (KubeVirt)
    - AI/ML (OpenShift AI)
```

**Deployment Topologies**:
| Topology | Use Case | Characteristics |
|----------|----------|-----------------|
| IPI (Installer-Provisioned) | Greenfield cloud | Automated infrastructure |
| UPI (User-Provisioned) | Existing infrastructure | Custom VM/network setup |
| SNO (Single Node) | Edge, development | All control + worker on one node |
| Compact | Remote offices | 3-node control + worker |
| Hypershift | Multi-tenancy | Hosted control planes |

### § 4.2 · RHEL Platform

**RHEL 9.4+ Highlights**:
| Feature | Specification | Business Impact |
|---------|---------------|-----------------|
| Kernel | Linux 5.14+ (backported) | Latest hardware support |
| Security | SELinux, FIPS 140-3 | Compliance-ready |
| Lifecycle | 10+ years support | Long-term stability |
| Container Tools | Podman, Buildah, Skopeo | Daemonless, rootless containers |
| System Roles | Ansible-driven management | Consistent configuration |
| Insights | Predictive analytics | Proactive issue resolution |

**RHEL Variants**:
```
RHEL Family:
├── RHEL Server (traditional)
├── RHEL for Edge (ostree-based, lightweight)
├── RHEL CoreOS (container-optimized, OpenShift nodes)
├── RHEL AI (foundation model platform)
└── Image Mode (bootable containers)
```

